Not even the freezing Cape Town weather can stop drinkers from getting a cold one. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Not even the freezing Cape Town weather can stop drinkers from getting a cold one. Alcohol and cigarettes are back on sale with the easing of lockdown regulations to level two. This comes after President Cyril Ramaphosa's announcement on Saturday evening. READ: Dlamini-Zuma clarifies regulations on sale of alcohol - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8am to 4pm, Monday to Friday Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.